Almost time for wine! I got through my supermarket trip earlier..just.  I decided rather than walking to our local one as I have done for 6 weeks, I would take my car to a bigger one to have more choice and be able to get more but it was awful. It was pretty quick to get in but once I was inside, it was way too busy which made it impossible to keep apart from the supermarket staff let alone the other people. I actually felt very anxious to be around so many people and I spent a fortune. I won't be doing that again but at least we will be very well stocked for a while. I even treated myself to these flowers. 
This afternoon I managed to move the ladders on the bunk beds by myself (with actual tools and stuff) so the room is finally finished. The Star Wars sheets arrived too so they have been washed and tumbled, ready for using tonight. The sheets are pretty bright and not very insta friendly but my boys really love them and that is the important thing. This afternoon we are hunkered down watching a film. It has been a long week but happy that we are all happy, safe and well. I hope you are too?

Growing up, this was one of my favorite dinners that my mom made and still is! ‚ô•Ô∏è In honor of Mother‚Äôs Day, sharing this easy ROASTED TOMATO & GARLIC PASTA.

HOW TO MAKE:
1/2 box pasta
2 pints of tomatoes 
3 cloves garlic
2 T. olive oil 
1/2 c. basil, chopped
S/P

Add tomatoes and whole garlic (still in wrapper, not peeled) to a glass baking dish or sheet pan. Toss with olive oil and S/P. Bake on 375 F for 25-30 minutes until tomatoes are blistered. While tomatoes are roasting, cook pasta according to box.

Once tomatoes are completely soft and blistered. Remove from oven. Peel garlic and smash. Toss tomato mixture with pasta. Top with basil.
